commit.message:
travis: test 9.6, drop 9.2

And try not to use a logfile called `log` which is the name of the log
directory in PG 10 (which isn't available in Travis yet.)
travis: install postgresql base package in addition to the -server-dev package
travis: test with pg 9.4 and pg 9.5, drop 9.1

Merge pull request #39 from saaros/compatibility

Compatibility improvements for PGDG rpms and OMcache

omcache use: set timeouts for commands instead of never waiting for writes

Previously all omcache calls using the libmemcached wrapper api (most of the
write commands) always had a timeout of `0` which meant that OMcache didn't
wait for results and just returned `MEMCACHED_BUFFERED` immediately.  That's
fine for some workloads but not ok for others, including the regression
tests.

Add a hardcoded non-zero timeout for writes for now, we should make this
runtime configurable at some point.  Requires currently unreleased OMcache.

rpm: use paths from pg_config for the files and allow suffix

This makes it easier to build pgmemcache rpms that work with the PGDG rpms
for various PostgreSQL versions.

For example:

    dnf install postgresql95-devel libomcache-devel
    make rpm rpm_name_suffix=95 USE_OMCACHE=1

travis: run different pg version tests as different jobs

Also run `apt-get update` in install phase to make sure package indexes are
up to date.
pgmemcache: release version 2.3.0
travis: build with pg 9.1, 9.2 and 9.3
travis: add .travis.yml for testing
localtests.sh: a script for running tests without installing

server_add: fix host string termination

Commit d6b22c0afc2 changed string argument handling, unfortunately it didn't
bother to make sure we zero-terminate the buffer passed to do_server_add.

Also adjusted the expected test output to match the new memcache_stats().

memcache_get_multi: refactor the code and fix warnings

Use DatumGetTextP(elem) to read text values from array instead of accessing
the Datums directly.  This silences a compiler warning and is the right
thing to do although it's unlikely that this makes a difference in practice
as keys are limited in size anyway (max 250 characters) and thus aren't
likely to be toasted, and DatumGetTextP() is basically just a cast for
non-toasted values.

Reduce #ifdef USE_OMCACHE/USE_LIBMEMCACHED hackery a bit and just copy the
loop separately for both implementations.  Use const unsigned char ** for
keys in OMcache and const char ** for keys in libmemcached.
pgmemcache.c: don't use XACT_EVENT_PRE_COMMIT in pg < 9.3 [#37]

README: updates about omcache and fixes for examples

* Mention OMcache as an optional replacement for libmemcached
* Fix trigger example to not use `NEW` in a delete trigger
* Reformat API listing and clarify some comments about it
* Update build instructions
* Update Credits section
README: rename to .rst and fix some formatting issues

Makefile: drop unnecessary build-deps and obsolete html target

yada hasn't been needed since commit e34b3a14d and bison and flex were
probably never needed.

pgmemcache.c: use consistent way of turning arguments to cstrings [#35]

Use VARDATA() and VARSIZE() - VARHDRSZ everywhere to avoid unnecessary
transformations and to allow binary keys everywhere.  Also use a common
function for checking key lengths and allow 250 character keys (previously
we only allowed 249 character keys due to a >= comparison.)
pgmemcache.c: no need to check arguments for null, the functions are strict

pgmemcache: simplify command handling a bit

Use a mask and switch for handling set commands.

Merge pull request #33 from saaros/omcache

pgmemcache: support building with omcache instead of libmemcached

pgmemcache: support building with omcache instead of libmemcached

Support for a new memcache client library, OMcache, in addition to
libmemcached which remains the default.  To build with OMcache install the
OMcache development packages and build with 'make USE_OMCACHE=1'.

OMcache build does not yet support all features, notably memcache_mget()
won't be available in OMcache builds.

See https://github.com/saaros/omcache for more information about OMcache.

Merge pull request #34 from saaros/coverity

Makefile: add a target for submitting builds to scan.coverity.com
Makefile: add a target for submitting builds to scan.coverity.com

Merge pull request #30 from saaros/buffer

Handle buffered requests
behaviors: reorganize the code a bit for clarity

behaviors: compare full behavior name, not just prefixes [#28]

get_memcached_behavior_flag et al were using strncmp to compare flags for an
unknown reason.  It caused flags with common prefixes to be compared
incorrectly, for example HASH_WITH_PREFIX_KEY was interpreted as HASH.

Revert to strcmp() instead which simplifies the code and fixes the issue.

Thanks olegdunkan for reporting the issue and suggesting a patch.

pgmemcache: flush client buffers on commit if configured so

Flush client buffers to memcache servers on commit if the new GUC
pgmemcache.flush_on_commit is enabled, otherwise some buffers may get
lost when the PostgreSQL backend terminates before everything has been
sent which is especially likely when the BUFFER_REQUESTS behavior is used.

set operations: return NULL on MEMCACHED_BUFFERED

Return NULL when a set-related function returns MEMCACHED_BUFFERED to
indicate that we don't really know the result of the action, but it wasn't
an error.

memcache_stats: write a row for each server even if we can't get stats

Refactored stats fetching function a bit to always write a line for each
defined server even if stat fetching fails.  Also changed the format a bit
with an empty line after each server instead of just one empty line at the
beginning of the stat output.
